<Link id="l00198" /><CodeLine lineNumber="198"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Class to represent struct types. There are two different kinds of struct</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00199" /><CodeLine lineNumber="199"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// types: Literal structs and Identified structs.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00200" /><CodeLine lineNumber="200"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00201" /><CodeLine lineNumber="201"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Literal struct types (e.g. &#123; i32, i32 &#125;) are uniqued structurally, and must</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00202" /><CodeLine lineNumber="202"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// always have a body when created.  You can get one of these by using one of</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00203" /><CodeLine lineNumber="203"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// the StructType::get() forms.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00204" /><CodeLine lineNumber="204"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00205" /><CodeLine lineNumber="205"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Identified structs (e.g. %foo or %42) may optionally have a name and are not</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00206" /><CodeLine lineNumber="206"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// uniqued.  The names for identified structs are managed at the LLVMContext</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00207" /><CodeLine lineNumber="207"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// level, so there can only be a single identified struct with a given name in</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00208" /><CodeLine lineNumber="208"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// a particular LLVMContext.  Identified structs may also optionally be opaque</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00209" /><CodeLine lineNumber="209"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// (have no body specified).  You get one of these by using one of the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00210" /><CodeLine lineNumber="210"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// StructType::create() forms.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00211" /><CodeLine lineNumber="211"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00212" /><CodeLine lineNumber="212"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Independent of what kind of struct you have, the body of a struct type are</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00213" /><CodeLine lineNumber="213"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// laid out in memory consecutively with the elements directly one after the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00214" /><CodeLine lineNumber="214"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// other (if the struct is packed) or (if not packed) with padding between the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00215" /><CodeLine lineNumber="215"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// elements as defined by DataLayout (which is required to match what the code</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00216" /><CodeLine lineNumber="216"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// generator for a target expects).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00217" /><CodeLine lineNumber="217"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00218" /><CodeLine lineNumber="218" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/structtype"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">class </span><span class="doxyHighlight">StructType : </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">public</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/type/#a817dfd76b27697e96a20f80f7bb68251">Type</a> &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00219" /><CodeLine lineNumber="219"><span class="doxyHighlight">  StructType(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/llvmcontext">LLVMContext</a> &amp;<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/callingconv/#ac6aa1387c4375260e2468eb5a77fdb4cafd841a49aec1539bc88abc8ff9e170fb">C</a>) : <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/demangle/itaniumdemangle-h/#a88ee8e4eea43084bd8964682683da88caa1fa27779242b4902f7ae3bdd5c6d508">Type</a>(<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/callingconv/#ac6aa1387c4375260e2468eb5a77fdb4cafd841a49aec1539bc88abc8ff9e170fb">C</a>, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/type/#a5e9e1c0dd93557be1b4ad72860f3cbdaa812a573d23fbb37aacd025e2a0588156">StructTyID</a>) &#123;&#125;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00428" /><CodeLine lineNumber="428"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// A fully specified VectorType is of the form &lt;vscale x n x Ty&gt;. &#39;n&#39; is the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00429" /><CodeLine lineNumber="429"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// minimum number of elements of type Ty contained within the vector, and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00430" /><CodeLine lineNumber="430"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// &#39;vscale x&#39; indicates that the total element count is an integer multiple</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00431" /><CodeLine lineNumber="431"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// of &#39;n&#39;, where the multiple is either guaranteed to be one, or is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00432" /><CodeLine lineNumber="432"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// statically unknown at compile time.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00433" /><CodeLine lineNumber="433"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00434" /><CodeLine lineNumber="434"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// If the multiple is known to be 1, then the extra term is discarded in</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00435" /><CodeLine lineNumber="435"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// textual IR:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00436" /><CodeLine lineNumber="436"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00437" /><CodeLine lineNumber="437"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// &lt;4 x i32&gt;          - a vector containing 4 i32s</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00438" /><CodeLine lineNumber="438"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// &lt;vscale x 4 x i32&gt; - a vector containing an unknown integer multiple</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00439" /><CodeLine lineNumber="439"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///                      of 4 i32s</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00440" /><CodeLine lineNumber="440"></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00447" /><CodeLine lineNumber="447"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// - For FixedVectorType = &lt;ElementQuantity x ty&gt;, there are</span></CodeLine>
